      {
        "title": "Dashboard Overview & Setup Guide",
        "text": {
          "content": "# ☕ Developer AI Tools: User Token Tracker\n\nThis specialized dashboard provides fine-grained, developer-level observability. It answers critical questions about **who** is calling which Gemini models, **how** frequently, and the specific consumption patterns of individual developers.\n\n### ⚙️ Why is this dashboard empty by default?\nBecause `agy` and other developer CLI tools run locally on workstations, their network calls communicate directly with the Vertex AI service. **These calls do not automatically write application-level logs into Google Cloud Logging.** To populate this dashboard, you must choose one of the following two standard patterns:\n\n* **Option 1: No-Code Audit Logs (Request Counts)**\n  Vertex AI Data Access Audit Logs are enabled in your project (`aiplatform.googleapis.com`). Our custom `user_tokens` metric parses these audit logs to extract the developer's email (`user_id`) and model (`model_id`). This tracks request counts but not exact token sizes (due to log privacy).\n  * **Troubleshooting:** If no data is shown, verify that your local CLI tool is fully authenticated using a Google Cloud account (e.g., via standard ADC or OAuth) rather than an AI Studio API key, and that you have `Private Logs Viewer` IAM permissions to view data access audit logs.\n\n* **Option 2: Lightweight Proxy (Exact Token Counts) 💎 [RECOMMENDED]**\n  Deploy our pre-built Cloud Run logging proxy. By setting `export VERTEX_API_ENDPOINT=\"https://your-proxy.a.run.app\"`, local CLI tools route traffic through the proxy, which logs the exact input, output, and cached token sizes for every developer. It is secure, private, and gives 100% precise token tracking!\n\n*See [USER_AND_USAGE_TRACKING_GUIDE.md](USER_AND_USAGE_TRACKING_GUIDE.md) and [HOW_TO_COLLECT_USER_DATA.md](HOW_TO_COLLECT_USER_DATA.md) for full deployment steps.*",
          "format": "MARKDOWN"
        }
      },
      {
        "title": "Token Consumption by User (Over Time)",
        "xyChart": {
          "dataSets": [
            {
              "timeSeriesQuery": {
                "timeSeriesFilter": {
                  "filter": "metric.type=\"logging.googleapis.com/user/user_tokens\"",
                  "aggregation": {
                    "alignmentPeriod": "60s",
                    "perSeriesAligner": "ALIGN_RATE",
                    "crossSeriesReducer": "REDUCE_SUM",
                    "groupByFields": [
                      "metric.label.user_id"
                    ]
                  }
                }
              },
              "plotType": "LINE",
              "targetAxis": "Y1"
            }
          ],
          "yAxis": {
            "label": "Tokens / Second (Rate)",
            "scale": "LINEAR"
          }
        }
      },
